{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf6d2ba21-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s53307"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"53307"},"text":"§ 53307.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Basis for determining gain or loss and for depreciating new vessels","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Under the income or excess profits tax laws of the United States, the basis for determining a gain or loss and for depreciation of a new vessel constructed, reconstructed, reconditioned, or acquired by the taxpayer, or for which purchase-money indebtedness is liquidated as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s53310"},"text":"section 53310 of this title","children":[],"tail":", with amounts from a construction reserve fund, shall be reduced by that part of the deposits in the fund expended in the construction, reconstruction, reconditioning, acquisition, or liquidation of purchase-money indebtedness of the new vessel that represents a gain not recognized for tax purposes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s53306"},"text":"section 53306 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf6d2ba22-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s8/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1589"},"text":"120 Stat. 1589","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf6d2ba23-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf6d2ba24-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width